                <mxCell id="legend" value="Per-node modules (each may be present):&#xa;• catchment_inflow (m³/day from CSV)&#xa;• evaporation (m³/day)&#xa;• drink_water demand → delivered + shortfall&#xa;• food_production (food_units × water_per_food_unit)&#xa;• energy: turbine flow × head_m × price_per_unit&#xa;&#xa;Edges carry: fraction (0..1) and delay (days)&#xa;&#xa;Note: this layout is illustrative — true topology lives in&#xa;horizon/data/topology/{nodes,edges}.csv and the demo&#xa;scenario.yaml at horizon/nrsm/scenarios/nile-mvp/." style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#cccccc;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="60" y="620" width="600" height="220" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
            </root>
        </mxGraphModel>
    </diagram>
</mxfile>